SIMPLE: bisulphate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bisulphate
<hw>Bi*sul"phate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>sulphate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
sulphate in which but half the hydrogen of the acid is replaced by a
positive element or radical, thus making the proportion of the acid to
the positive or basic portion twice what it is in the normal sulphates;
an acid sulphate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bisulphide</ent>⟦br⟧
